[761.311208, "o", "mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b["]
[761.311336, "o", "1m-c\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-a\u001b[0m \u001b[4mrounds\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-C\u001b[0m \u001b[4mcomment\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4mkeyfile\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-P\u001b[0m \u001b[4mpassphrase\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-l\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-v\u001b[0m] [\u001b[1m-E\u001b[0m \u001b[4mfingerprint_hash\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4minput_keyfile\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-B\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4minput_keyfile\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-D\u001b[0m \u001b[4mpkcs11\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-F\u001b[0m \u001b[4mhostname\u001b[24m [\u001b[1m-lv\u001b[0m] [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4mknown_hosts_file\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-H\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4mknown_hosts_file\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[19;1H     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-K\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-a\u001b[0m \u001b[4mrounds\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-w\u001b[0m \u001b[4mprovider\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-R\u001b[0m \u001b[4mhostname\u001b[24m [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4mknown_hosts_file\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-r\u001b[0m \u001b[4mhostname\u001b[24m [\u001b[1m-g\u001b[0m] [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4minput_keyfile\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-M\u001b[0m \u001b[1mgenerate\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-O\u001b[0m \u001b[4moption\u001b[24m] \u001b[4moutput_file\u001b[24m"]
[761.311349, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m \u001b[1m-M\u001b[0m \u001b[1mscreen\u001b[0m [\u001b[1m-f\u001b[0m \u001b[4minput_file\u001b[24m] [\u001b[1m-O\u001b[0m \u001b[4moption\u001b[24m] \u001b[4moutput_file\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh-keygen(1) line 9 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[763.905664, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[763.905874, "o", "...skipping...\r\n     The type of key to be generated is specified with the \u001b[1m\u001b[7m-t\u001b[27m\u001b[0m option.  If in‐\u001b[m\r\n     voked without any arguments, \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m will generate an RSA key.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m is also used to generate groups for use in Diffie-Hellman group\u001b[m\r\n     exchange (DH-GEX).  See the \u001b[4mMODULI\u001b[24m \u001b[4mGENERATION\u001b[24m section for details.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     Finally, \u001b[1mssh-keygen\u001b[0m can be used to generate and update Key Revocation\u001b[m\r\n     Lists, and to test whether given keys have been revoked by one.  See the\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4mKEY\u001b[24m \u001b[4mREVOCATION\u001b[24m \u001b[4mLISTS\u001b[24m section for details.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     Normally each user wishing to use SSH with public key authentication runs\u001b[m\r\n     this once to create the authentication key in \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_dsa\u001b[24m,\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ecdsa\u001b[24m, \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ecdsa_sk\u001b[24m, \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ed25519\u001b[24m,\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_ed25519_sk\u001b[24m or \u001b[4m~/.ssh/id_rsa\u001b[24m.  Additionally, the system adminis‐\u001b[m\r\n     trator may use"]
[763.90588, "o", " this to generate host keys.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     Normally this program generates the key and asks for a file in which to\u001b[m\r\n     store the private key.  The public key is stored in a file with the same\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh-keygen(1) line 47 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[773.362803, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[773.363252, "o", "...skipping...\r\n             \u001b[1mverify\u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[7m-t\u001b[27m\u001b[0m\u001b[1mime\u001b[0m=\u001b[4mtimestamp\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n                     Specifies a time to use when validating signatures instead\u001b[m\r\n                     of the current time.  The time may be specified as a date\u001b[m\r\n                     or time in the YYYYMMDD[Z] or in YYYYMMDDHHMM[SS][Z] for‐\u001b[m\r\n                     mats.  Dates and times will be interpreted in the current\u001b[m\r\n                     system time zone unless suffixed with a Z character, which\u001b[m\r\n                     causes them to be interpreted in the UTC time zone.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             The \u001b[1m-O\u001b[0m option may be specified multiple times.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-P\u001b[0m \u001b[4mpassphrase\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             Provides the (old) passphrase.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-p\u001b[0m      Requests changing the passphrase of a private key file instead of\u001b[m\r\n             creating a new private key.  The program will prompt for the file\u001b[m\r\n             containing the private key, for the old passphrase, and twice for\u001b[m\r"]
[773.36327, "o", "\n             the new passphrase.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh-keygen(1) line 265 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[774.435231, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[774.435393, "o", "...skipping...\r\n     \u001b[1m\u001b[7m-t\u001b[27m\u001b[0m \u001b[1mdsa\u001b[0m | \u001b[1mecdsa\u001b[0m | \u001b[1mecdsa-sk\u001b[0m | \u001b[1med25519\u001b[0m | \u001b[1med25519-sk\u001b[0m | \u001b[1mrsa\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n             Specifies the type of key to create.  The possible values are\u001b[m\r\n             “dsa”, “ecdsa”, “ecdsa-sk”, “ed25519”, “ed25519-sk”, or “rsa”.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n             This flag may also be used to specify the desired signature type\u001b[m\r\n             when signing certificates using an RSA CA key.  The available RSA\u001b[m\r\n             signature variants are “ssh-rsa” (SHA1 signatures, not recom‐\u001b[m\r\n             mended), “rsa-sha2-256”, and “rsa-sha2-512” (the default).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-U\u001b[0m      When used in combination with \u001b[1m-s\u001b[0m or \u001b[1m-Y\u001b[0m \u001b[1msign\u001b[0m, this option indicates\u001b[m\r\n             that a CA key resides in a ssh-agent(1).  See the \u001b[4mCERTIFICATES\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n             section for more information.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-u\u001b[0m      Update a KRL.  When specified with \u001b[1m-k\u001b[0m, keys listed via the command"]
[774.435406, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n             line are added to the existing KRL rather than a new KRL being\u001b[m\r\n             created.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n     \u001b[1m-V\u001b[0m \u001b[4mvalidity_interval\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page ssh-keygen(1) line 305 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
